cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COMM, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the concept of unequal error protection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the effect of feedback on error protection, which falls under the sub-category cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The use of block codes and discrete memoryless channels suggests the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions variable-length block codes, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
